Part B: Chi-Square Goodness-of-Fit Test

1. Create columns: BMI Category, Observed, Expected, (O−E)²/E.

2. Observed Values:
   =COUNTIF(data_range, category)

3. Expected Values:
   =SUM(observed_range) / number_of_categories

4. Chi-Square Calculation:
   =(Observed - Expected)^2 / Expected

5. Final Results:
   - Chi-Square Statistic:
     =SUM(calculated_values)
   - P-Value:
     =CHISQ.TEST(observed_range, expected_range)


